# Go Core Rules

- Keep exported C ABI functions minimal and stable in `core/internal/ffi/`.
- Keep daemon control-plane contracts explicit and backward-compatible for UI compatibility.
- Keep runtime lifecycle/state transitions behind explicit boundaries (start/stop and controlled reload/update paths).
- Keep TUN lifecycle decoupled from outbound switching logic.
- Use context cancellation and structured error propagation for long-running routines.
- Avoid importing UI concerns into the core module.
- Keep core daemon as owner of runtime config persistence and subscription/rule resolution.
- When generating sing-box runtime config, use latest non-deprecated fields only (see `21-singbox-latest-config.mdc`).
- In Rule V2, treat `baseRules + composedRules` as source of truth for UI editing, and compile/resolve them to `rules` at apply time.

## Example

```go
// GOOD: daemon worker shutdown with context cancellation
ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())
defer cancel()
```
